snippet.textDisplay:
Why would you want a Qawwali to be a discoish funky song!! I had high regard for Fuad. But TBH It's a disaster! Just call it another disco mix but don't you guys effing dare to call it Qawwali!! Should have learned from Pakistani/Indian Coke studio how they have reproduced Qawwalis. #Disappointed
Apparently, tesher alone can produce better-mixed qawwali than the whole team of Coke Studio Bangla! At least I can still vibe with tesher's qawwali mix!
Reference: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=GW9sM-l1bvg

snippet.textDisplay:
Ok, hold on...hold on.... let me just take a breath here, 'cause I can't keep quiet about this anymore, man! This experimental fusion of Funk and Pop with Bangla qawwali is straight-up mind-blowing, man. #Fuad is showing us what he's capable of when he's given the right resources. This composition is out of this world, I'm telling you.

Those fat basslines, the funky + kawali grooves, the transitions, the epic drum fills, the mind-blowing grooves, and let's not forget the killer saxophone work. The composition flows so smoothly, and that guitar solo fits in perfectly. And damn, that beatbox and the way vocal chops are used, it's on point.

The timing is excellent, and that harmonizing part in the middle just blows my mind, man. And let's give some props to Mueshidabadi, Tashfee, and Shuchona Shely for singing their hearts out. They nailed it, man! But let's not forget, Shayan Chowdhury #Arnob is the man behind this magical creation.

I swear, I haven't learned this much from any Bangla experimental fusion before. It's just something else, man!

#CokeStudioBanglaseason2
#RealMagic
